(0,'Partner plank band row','The partner plank band row is an abdominal exercise where two partners perform single-arm planks while pulling on the opposite ends of an exercise band. This technique can be done for time or reps in any ab-focused workout.','Strength','Abdominals','Bands','Intermediate',0,NULL),
(1,'Banded crunch isometric hold','The banded crunch isometric hold is an exercise targeting the abdominal muscles, particularly the rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles. The band adds resistance and continuous tension to this popular exercise.','Strength','Abdominals','Bands','Intermediate',NULL,NULL),
(2,'FYR Banded Plank Jack','The banded plank jack is a variation on the plank that involves moving the legs in and out for repetitions. Having a band around the thighs forces the lower body to work harder, particularly the hips and glutes. The plank jack is commonly performed as part of a bodyweight circuit, or as part of a dynamic warm-up.','Strength','Abdominals','Bands','Intermediate',NULL,NULL),
